subSubSection.paragraph:
Size
. The largest specimen examined is a female with a carapace length of 64.0 mm (postorbital carapace length of 
49.9 mm
). The largest male is second form and has a carapace length of 60.0 mm (postorbital carapace length of 
45.7 mm
). The smallest first form male has a carapace length of 
35.2 mm
(postorbital carapace length of 
26.6 mm
). Sizes of ovigerous females and females carrying young are not available as none have been found.
